commit 12b626fae3efc5e976865b5bc7929007d9df97f4
Author: Michael J. Chudobiak <mjc@svn.gnome.org>
Date:	2008-07-30

    Removed the "Delete Comment" function, because the comments are
    now linked

    2008-07-30	Michael J. Chudobiak  <mjc@svn.gnome.org>

	    * src/gth-browser-ui.h:
	    * src/gth-browser.c: (window_update_sensitivity):
	    * src/gth-viewer-ui.h:
	    * src/gth-window-actions-callbacks.c:
	    * src/gth-window-actions-callbacks.h:
	    * src/gth-window-actions-entries.h:
	    Removed the "Delete Comment" function, because the comments
	    are
	    now linked to the embedded image metadata. Deleting the
	    comments
	    would mean deleting quite a few metadata fields, which is
	    probably too invasive. Use the "Edit Comment" function
	    instead.
	    Might need to revisit this issue.


    svn path=/trunk/; revision=2362

