M	NEWS

commit 091629325beb475e769323becb8db2ac305e7ef7
Author: Michael J. Chudobiak <mjc@cvs.gnome.org>
Date:	2007-05-11

    Do not use the "failed" thumbnail if it was generated in the last 5

    2007-05-11	Michael J. Chudobiak  <mjc@cvs.gnome.org>

	    * libgthumb/thumb-loader.c: (thumb_loader_init),
	    (thumb_loader_start__step2), (thumb_loader_save_to_cache),
	    (thumb_loader_done_cb), (thumb_loader_error_cb):
	    Do not use the "failed" thumbnail if it was generated in the
	    last 5 seconds. Instead, try to thumbnail it again. Also, read
	    the image file mtime once and save it in the private data,
	    rather than reading it several times (which may give different
	    values). The two changes fix bug 432759.

	    * libgthumb/thumb-loader.h: Deleted unused functions.


    svn path=/trunk/; revision=1652

M	ChangeLog
M	libgthumb/thumb-loader.c
M	libgthumb/thumb-loader.h

commit 44d2996aea84df6a0b39ca729882345eb601e2f2
Author: Michael J. Chudobiak <mjc@cvs.gnome.org>
Date:	2007-05-11

    Do not check for orientation if the loaders failed.

    2007-05-11	Michael J. Chudobiak  <mjc@cvs.gnome.org>

	    * libgthumb/file-utils.c: (gth_pixbuf_new_from_uri):
	    Do not check for orientation if the loaders failed.


    svn path=/trunk/; revision=1650

M	ChangeLog
M	libgthumb/file-utils.c

commit 2ccc1b7d5a764da2a48427ec93207deb2d9a8e15
Author: Michael J. Chudobiak <mjc@cvs.gnome.org>
Date:	2007-05-11

    Backport from metadata-ideas branch. Move orientation-checking of new

    2007-05-11	Michael J. Chudobiak  <mjc@cvs.gnome.org>

	    * libgthumb/file-utils.c:
	    (get_pixbuf_using_external_converter),
	    (gth_pixbuf_new_from_uri):
	    * libgthumb/image-loader.c: (image_loader_finalize__step2),
	    (image_loader_set_pixbuf), (image_loader_sync_pixbuf):
	    Backport from metadata-ideas branch. Move orientation-checking
	    of new pixbufs from image_loader_sync_pixbuf to
	    gth_pixbuf_new_from_uri,
	    where all the other image loading trickery is. Also, added
	    support for
	    gdk-pixbuf reporting of orientation tags (bug 428725,
	    patch pending)
	    instead of using libexif. This will provide new orientation
	    tag
	    support for tiff images.


    svn path=/trunk/; revision=1649

M	ChangeLog
M	libgthumb/file-utils.c
M	libgthumb/image-loader.c

